WEBVTT

00:00:01.724 --> 00:00:03.391
The rest of you
are to accompany me!

00:00:03.559 --> 00:00:04.143
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

00:00:04.225 --> 00:00:06.019
Leave the bodies
of the dead for later!

00:00:06.185 --> 00:00:07.937
Transporting the injured
is our top priority!

00:00:08.731 --> 00:00:09.690
We've got a critical patient here!

00:00:09.772 --> 00:00:11.774
Please take him to room 203!

00:00:18.073 --> 00:00:19.158
Captain Unohana...

00:00:20.408 --> 00:00:21.909
was it really the right choice

00:00:21.993 --> 00:00:23.954
for us to remain in
the Squad 4 barracks?

00:00:24.829 --> 00:00:27.124
We could've saved more lives if we
were out there in the Seireitei

00:00:27.207 --> 00:00:28.875
- with the rest of—
- Isane.

00:00:29.792 --> 00:00:32.463
You shouldn't let your feelings
dictate what you say.

00:00:33.088 --> 00:00:36.549
It would have been easy for us to
vacate this place out of concern.

00:00:38.509 --> 00:00:42.305
But I know you are
not so short-sighted

00:00:42.389 --> 00:00:45.808
that I have to explain
why that would have been wrong.

00:00:47.561 --> 00:00:48.561
Yes, ma'am...

00:00:49.021 --> 00:00:51.856
I'm...very sorry...!

00:00:52.649 --> 00:00:54.984
There's no need to cry, Isane...

00:00:56.111 --> 00:00:59.531
"Do not leave the Squad 4 barracks.
No matter what."

00:01:00.908 --> 00:01:07.998
That was the final order given
to us by the Head Captain...

00:01:37.986 --> 00:01:42.783
<i>The blue skies above are hopelessly clear</i>

00:01:42.865 --> 00:01:47.954
<i>At my wit's end, I feel a growing frustration</i>

00:01:48.371 --> 00:01:52.793
<i>As if to laugh at us hopeless cowards</i>

00:01:53.126 --> 00:01:56.629
<i>Countless eyes stare at us</i>

00:01:57.088 --> 00:02:02.969
<i>This soul of mine breaks again and again</i>

00:02:03.262 --> 00:02:06.181
<i>All I can do is hold it tight</i>

00:02:07.390 --> 00:02:12.395
<i>Until the day it turns to ash</i>

00:02:12.645 --> 00:02:15.274
<i>I've absorbed all of this sorrow</i>

00:02:15.399 --> 00:02:19.902
<i>It has shaped me, painted me</i>

00:02:20.027 --> 00:02:22.739
<i>But that's how we got here, right?</i>

00:02:22.865 --> 00:02:27.703
<i>One step at a time, just like breathing</i>

00:02:27.828 --> 00:02:30.247
<i>These countless scars on my palm</i>

00:02:30.372 --> 00:02:32.248
<i>That no longer fade</i>

00:02:32.373 --> 00:02:36.002
<i>Are my badge, my story</i>

00:02:36.294 --> 00:02:39.965
<i>I faced the fear and shred it to pieces</i>

00:02:40.090 --> 00:02:43.050
<i>And let it walk beside me once more</i>

00:02:43.134 --> 00:02:48.014
BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:03:00.776 --> 00:03:01.777
Here you go, sir.

00:03:02.361 --> 00:03:04.531
According to this message
sent by Kisuke Urahara,

00:03:05.032 --> 00:03:10.913
he, Orihime Inoue,
and Yasutora Sado are all safe.

00:03:11.580 --> 00:03:12.830
However,
further details are unknown...

00:03:13.581 --> 00:03:14.582
I see...

00:03:16.543 --> 00:03:18.002
Let me go, you idiot!

00:03:18.502 --> 00:03:19.503
The Captain...

00:03:19.587 --> 00:03:20.713
There's no way Captain Zaraki

00:03:20.796 --> 00:03:21.840
- would lose!
- Please calm down!

00:03:21.924 --> 00:03:22.925
- You need rest.
- Captain!

00:03:23.008 --> 00:03:24.383
- Get me a sedative! Hurry!
- Ichigo!

00:03:25.009 --> 00:03:27.054
Come over here, Ichigo.

00:03:27.387 --> 00:03:28.472
You need medical treatment.

00:03:28.847 --> 00:03:30.014
No, I'm fine.

00:03:30.431 --> 00:03:32.516
I already got some first-aid.

00:03:32.935 --> 00:03:33.977
No, it's not okay!

00:03:34.144 --> 00:03:37.104
I can tell that
you're badly wounded.

00:03:38.064 --> 00:03:39.066
Ichigo...

00:03:39.942 --> 00:03:42.401
Rukia and Abarai
have gotten out of surgery.

00:03:43.402 --> 00:03:44.612
TRAUMA ROOM

00:03:44.695 --> 00:03:45.197
TRAUMA ROOM
They're no longer
in critical condition

00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:46.907
They're no longer
in critical condition

00:03:47.366 --> 00:03:48.741
and are now stable.

00:03:49.951 --> 00:03:51.245
Please call me
if anything comes up.

00:03:55.373 --> 00:03:56.832
- Ichigo...
- Rukia!

00:03:57.084 --> 00:03:58.835
Is it all right for you to talk?!

00:03:59.669 --> 00:04:02.505
She just said
our condition was stable...

00:04:03.339 --> 00:04:05.591
Weren't you listening, you idiot?

00:04:05.759 --> 00:04:06.759
Oh yeah...?

00:04:07.052 --> 00:04:08.928
It seems your mouth
is working just fine...

00:04:10.805 --> 00:04:11.807
Ichigo...

00:04:12.848 --> 00:04:15.685
You came to protect
the Soul Society, didn't you?

00:04:16.687 --> 00:04:17.687
Thank you...

00:04:17.853 --> 00:04:18.771
Of course!

00:04:19.189 --> 00:04:22.401
Though,
I couldn't do anything this time...

00:04:22.858 --> 00:04:23.860
You dumbass...

00:04:24.151 --> 00:04:26.612
You drove the enemy boss away!

00:04:27.488 --> 00:04:30.783
If you hadn't come,
things would have been even worse.

00:04:31.826 --> 00:04:33.954
You should be holding
your head up high, you idiot!

00:04:34.913 --> 00:04:35.913
Hirako...

00:04:37.915 --> 00:04:39.166
Mr. Ichigo Kurosaki!

00:04:39.625 --> 00:04:41.043
Captain Kurotsuchi
would like to see you.

00:04:41.545 --> 00:04:42.754
It's about your Zanpakuto...

00:04:46.925 --> 00:04:50.678
Typical. He's always busy
no matter what the situation is.

00:04:51.762 --> 00:04:54.975
Ignoring his wounds and caring
for everybody but himself.

00:04:56.935 --> 00:04:57.935
Captain Hirako...

00:04:58.812 --> 00:05:02.899
I wonder why Ichigo had
such a painful look on his face...

00:05:03.567 --> 00:05:05.735
It seems he had
a rough time as well.

00:05:06.903 --> 00:05:08.904
His Zanpakuto was broken,

00:05:09.072 --> 00:05:11.324
and in the end,
he couldn't protect anybody.

00:05:11.949 --> 00:05:13.160
He's probably exhausted.

00:05:13.701 --> 00:05:14.952
There's no need to worry.

00:05:16.704 --> 00:05:20.416
Do you really think...that's it?

00:05:22.586 --> 00:05:24.713
I feel as if he's dealing with

00:05:25.838 --> 00:05:28.966
something more serious
and he's trying to hide it...

00:05:33.346 --> 00:05:36.350
The Head Captain's body
couldn't be found.

00:05:37.892 --> 00:05:40.394
The enemy destroyed everything...

00:05:43.857 --> 00:05:45.358
I have a report.

00:05:45.901 --> 00:05:48.612
Squad 6 Captain Byakuya Kuchiki

00:05:48.694 --> 00:05:51.740
and Squad 11 Captain
Kenpachi Zaraki

00:05:52.240 --> 00:05:53.992
have both survived.

00:05:54.951 --> 00:05:56.995
However,
it will be difficult for them

00:05:57.079 --> 00:05:58.872
to return to their duties
as captains...

00:05:59.497 --> 00:06:01.750
They may never
regain consciousness...

00:06:01.833 --> 00:06:02.834
Get out!

00:06:03.168 --> 00:06:05.252
I don't want to hear
such reports right now!

00:06:05.711 --> 00:06:08.714
Can't you see that
we lost the Head Captain?

00:06:09.423 --> 00:06:11.802
What more do you want us
to deal with?!

00:06:11.884 --> 00:06:13.595
Stop.
You're embarrassing yourself.

00:06:13.677 --> 00:06:14.930
Easy for you to say!

00:06:15.180 --> 00:06:17.807
I know you and others held a grudge
against the Head Captain!

00:06:17.891 --> 00:06:19.434
That's why you can stay so calm!

00:06:19.810 --> 00:06:21.144
How dare you...!

00:06:21.310 --> 00:06:22.687
Stop, Soi Fon!

00:06:23.312 --> 00:06:25.899
Do you think you're the only one
who wants to scream?!

00:06:27.483 --> 00:06:30.737
Now, now, now, now...

00:06:30.903 --> 00:06:32.738
No fighting.

00:06:33.865 --> 00:06:35.492
If Old Man Yama was still here,

00:06:35.574 --> 00:06:38.702
he would've lined us up
and smacked us for sure.

00:06:39.579 --> 00:06:42.624
He'd then say, "How pathetic
to see you cry and scream

00:06:42.706 --> 00:06:44.250
in front of
the articles I left behind!"

00:06:44.834 --> 00:06:46.086
Kyoraku, you bastard...

00:06:46.168 --> 00:06:47.963
The Thirteen Court Guard Squads...

00:06:48.838 --> 00:06:50.632
doesn't exist to grieve the dead

00:06:50.714 --> 00:06:53.175
or cry over the destruction
of the Soul Society.

00:06:54.636 --> 00:06:57.389
It exists to protect
the Soul Society.

00:06:59.141 --> 00:07:00.766
Let's try to look forward.

00:07:01.435 --> 00:07:03.812
We <i>are</i> the Thirteen
Court Guard Squads, aren't we?

00:07:05.855 --> 00:07:06.857
"Can't fix it"?

00:07:07.189 --> 00:07:08.190
Why not?!

00:07:08.733 --> 00:07:12.237
You fix your Zanpakuto whenever
it gets broken, don't you?!

00:07:12.778 --> 00:07:14.322
Are you stupid?

00:07:14.531 --> 00:07:16.658
I don't "fix" mine.

00:07:16.740 --> 00:07:18.742
I "modify" it.

00:07:19.452 --> 00:07:21.579
The only thing
that can fix a Zanpakuto

00:07:21.663 --> 00:07:24.624
is its owner's mind,
Spiritual Pressure,

00:07:24.708 --> 00:07:28.377
and time to infuse them
into your Zanpakuto.

00:07:28.670 --> 00:07:29.920
That's all.

00:07:31.714 --> 00:07:32.716
Fine...

00:07:33.007 --> 00:07:36.636
So you're saying I should
take it back and fix it myself.

00:07:37.052 --> 00:07:39.555
Let me finish explaining.

00:07:40.891 --> 00:07:42.809
I was only talking about Shikai.

00:07:42.892 --> 00:07:45.687
The destruction of a Zanpakuto's
Shikai and Bankai

00:07:45.769 --> 00:07:47.646
have completely different meanings.

00:07:48.355 --> 00:07:52.276
A destroyed Bankai
can <i>never</i> be restored.

00:07:52.694 --> 00:07:54.196
What?!

00:07:55.237 --> 00:07:56.865
Then what should I do?

00:07:59.408 --> 00:08:00.410
It's me.

00:08:04.538 --> 00:08:05.956
- Come back here!
- Catch him!

00:08:06.040 --> 00:08:07.500
- Kon?!
- Nooo!

00:08:07.584 --> 00:08:10.920
I hadn't seen him in a while,
but he was in the Soul Society?

00:08:11.879 --> 00:08:12.838
I see...

00:08:12.923 --> 00:08:14.173
I thought so.

00:08:14.841 --> 00:08:15.759
All right.

00:08:15.841 --> 00:08:17.093
I'm on my way.

00:08:18.094 --> 00:08:20.514
Come with me, Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:08:21.514 --> 00:08:23.307
You should meet them.

00:08:23.682 --> 00:08:26.561
Although I don't want to
in the slightest.

00:08:27.312 --> 00:08:29.730
The great Squad Zero is coming.

00:08:34.068 --> 00:08:35.070
Hirako!

00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:37.905
Came to check it out too, Ichigo?

00:08:38.322 --> 00:08:40.115
I don't really recommend it.

00:08:41.826 --> 00:08:43.953
So where's this Squad Zero
coming from?

00:08:44.245 --> 00:08:47.749
I mean, they're only showing up now
after the Seireitei got destroyed?

00:08:48.250 --> 00:08:49.833
Where do they usually stay?

00:08:50.418 --> 00:08:51.711
In the Royal Palace.

00:08:51.878 --> 00:08:54.505
Is that not within the Seireitei?

00:08:55.423 --> 00:08:57.716
Do you remember how those walls
came falling from the sky

00:08:57.801 --> 00:08:58.884
when you first came here?

00:09:00.595 --> 00:09:03.722
Those walls have been
surrounding this area

00:09:03.807 --> 00:09:06.809
since things have been chaotic
in the Seireitei lately.

00:09:07.059 --> 00:09:11.730
It was originally meant to surround
the Seireitei during emergencies.

00:09:12.731 --> 00:09:13.774
So then...

00:09:13.942 --> 00:09:16.360
If it's meant to protect
the Seireitei during emergencies,

00:09:16.653 --> 00:09:18.989
what does this wall
normally protect?

00:09:20.698 --> 00:09:21.865
Look, they're coming.

00:09:30.917 --> 00:09:31.918
What is that?!

00:09:32.251 --> 00:09:33.378
Tenchuren...

00:09:34.211 --> 00:09:36.798
It's Squad Zero's
transport vehicle.

00:09:37.841 --> 00:09:40.217
Squad Zero consists of
five total members.

00:09:41.510 --> 00:09:42.511
Just five?!

00:09:43.138 --> 00:09:44.139
They have no squad officers.

00:09:44.597 --> 00:09:45.889
All five are captains.

00:09:46.975 --> 00:09:47.975
Also...

00:09:48.350 --> 00:09:50.312
...the combined strength
of those five...

00:09:51.895 --> 00:09:54.190
...is greater than that of the entire
Thirteen Court Guard Squads.

00:10:21.384 --> 00:10:22.552
Hell yeah!

00:10:22.635 --> 00:10:25.346
We're here, we're here!
We're finally here!

00:10:26.806 --> 00:10:29.433
Squad Zero's in the house!

00:10:30.100 --> 00:10:32.937
Long time no see, you fledglings of
the Thirteen Court Guard Squads!

00:10:33.020 --> 00:10:34.563
Have you been eating right,
getting enough sleep,

00:10:34.648 --> 00:10:36.399
- and staying healthy?
- These guys are pretty different

00:10:36.482 --> 00:10:38.275
from what I had in mind...

00:10:39.610 --> 00:10:41.028
The hell was that for?!

00:10:41.446 --> 00:10:43.657
It's been a while, Shinji!

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:45.658
Hiyori isn't with you?

00:10:45.908 --> 00:10:47.660
- How rare!
- "It's been a while"?

00:10:47.744 --> 00:10:49.245
I don't know you—

00:10:49.328 --> 00:10:51.121
Wait... "Hiyori"?

00:10:51.623 --> 00:10:53.332
Have you forgotten who I am?!

00:10:53.750 --> 00:10:55.793
It's me, Kirio!

00:10:55.918 --> 00:10:57.836
<i>Y-You're</i> Ms. Kirio?!

00:10:58.171 --> 00:11:01.131
Seriously?! You're like
a completely different person!

00:11:01.216 --> 00:11:05.302
Oh, Shinji!
I haven't changed <i>that</i> much!

00:11:06.513 --> 00:11:08.222
Ah, I'm starving!

00:11:12.769 --> 00:11:15.855
Hey! It's been a while,
hasn't it, Unohana?

00:11:16.523 --> 00:11:19.400
So, the healing techniques
I taught you...

00:11:19.484 --> 00:11:21.193
Are you putting them to good use?

00:11:21.360 --> 00:11:22.445
Of course.

00:11:22.611 --> 00:11:23.947
Really?!

00:11:24.197 --> 00:11:28.576
Because I heard you guys
just lost a bunch of men!

00:11:28.743 --> 00:11:30.703
So what's the story there?

00:11:32.080 --> 00:11:33.623
Now, now!

00:11:33.706 --> 00:11:35.625
It's been so long
since you've seen one another!

00:11:35.708 --> 00:11:37.376
I'm sure you have
a ton of catching up to do,

00:11:37.460 --> 00:11:38.586
but save it for later!

00:11:40.587 --> 00:11:41.589
Well now...

00:11:41.673 --> 00:11:45.092
I see everyone in Squad Zero
is the same as always, Osho!

00:11:45.802 --> 00:11:49.639
So what business do you have
for coming here this time?

00:11:50.682 --> 00:11:51.682
Hmm...

00:11:52.683 --> 00:11:54.686
So you're Ichigo Kurosaki, huh?

00:11:56.770 --> 00:11:59.816
We came here to rebuild
the Thirteen Court Guard Squads

00:11:59.899 --> 00:12:01.609
at the behest of the Soul King.

00:12:02.610 --> 00:12:07.657
For starters, Ichigo Kurosaki,
we're taking you back up with us.

00:12:08.158 --> 00:12:09.241
Are you kidding me?!

00:12:09.868 --> 00:12:11.952
I don't care how important
Squad Zero is,

00:12:12.578 --> 00:12:13.788
but you were relaxing above

00:12:13.871 --> 00:12:15.789
while the Seireitei
was getting destroyed.

00:12:16.124 --> 00:12:17.125
But now, you come down,

00:12:17.207 --> 00:12:18.876
wanting to rebuild
the Thirteen Court Guard Squads?!

00:12:19.543 --> 00:12:21.171
Quit joking around!

00:12:22.629 --> 00:12:24.506
Let's continue.

00:12:24.591 --> 00:12:25.716
- So...
- Hey!

00:12:26.551 --> 00:12:28.052
Shut up.

00:12:28.595 --> 00:12:30.179
<i>What kind of move was that?</i>

00:12:30.721 --> 00:12:33.224
"Quit joking around"?
That's our line.

00:12:33.725 --> 00:12:35.225
What were you again?

00:12:35.726 --> 00:12:38.187
The Thirteen Court Guard Squads.
Am I right?

00:12:38.730 --> 00:12:41.356
Our job is to protect
the Royal Palace.

00:12:41.732 --> 00:12:44.402
Your job is to protect
the Seireitei.

00:12:45.235 --> 00:12:47.654
What kind of Court Guard
cries for help

00:12:47.739 --> 00:12:50.283
after failing to get the job done?

00:12:50.616 --> 00:12:52.869
You're not worthy
to bear that name.

00:12:54.620 --> 00:12:56.371
That hurts, damn it!

00:12:57.831 --> 00:13:00.083
I told you to save it for later.

00:13:00.668 --> 00:13:03.462
Let's finish
what we came here for first.

00:13:03.546 --> 00:13:04.589
No need.

00:13:04.672 --> 00:13:05.756
Huh?

00:13:06.090 --> 00:13:08.717
Everything on the list of things
we need to take with us...

00:13:08.967 --> 00:13:10.886
They're all here.

00:13:14.890 --> 00:13:17.268
All that is remaining is you...

00:13:19.687 --> 00:13:21.063
Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:13:21.898 --> 00:13:22.981
Unacceptable.

00:13:23.774 --> 00:13:26.318
The three people
inside your spheres

00:13:26.402 --> 00:13:29.989
are in no condition to leave
the Seireitei right now.

00:13:30.615 --> 00:13:32.783
I cannot allow you
to take them with you.

00:13:35.953 --> 00:13:38.413
That's exactly why
we're taking them with us!

00:13:39.499 --> 00:13:41.333
I'm sure you're well aware

00:13:42.168 --> 00:13:45.754
that you're not strong enough
to fully restore these three.

00:13:47.381 --> 00:13:50.259
You already know, don't you, Retsu?

00:13:51.219 --> 00:13:55.682
Medical care isn't what
you should be doing right now.

00:13:59.351 --> 00:14:01.812
You broke into my lab as well, huh?

00:14:02.897 --> 00:14:06.442
As always,
you're so disrespectful.

00:14:07.277 --> 00:14:10.572
Oh, why if it isn't Mayuri.

00:14:10.904 --> 00:14:14.576
As always, you exaggerate
by calling it a break-in.

00:14:14.616 --> 00:14:18.871
When I placed my hand on the door,
it just slid right open.

00:14:19.831 --> 00:14:20.831
However...

00:14:21.124 --> 00:14:25.003
it was far less secure
than when I was around.

00:14:26.796 --> 00:14:28.255
H-Hold on a second!

00:14:28.798 --> 00:14:30.341
Why are you taking me as well?!

00:14:30.799 --> 00:14:34.177
I can recover from these injuries
just fine in the Seireitei!

00:14:36.139 --> 00:14:37.389
We know that.

00:14:37.599 --> 00:14:40.809
You're the only one being taken
for a different reason.

00:14:41.436 --> 00:14:42.644
"A different reason"?

00:14:42.979 --> 00:14:44.605
<i>Hello there!</i>

00:14:44.938 --> 00:14:47.734
<i>Well, it's been a while</i>
<i>since I've seen you all!</i>

00:14:47.900 --> 00:14:49.277
<i>I'm sure you must have</i>
<i>been worried.</i>

00:14:49.818 --> 00:14:51.738
<i>I'm so sorry about that.</i>

00:14:52.404 --> 00:14:53.405
<i>Huh?</i>

00:14:53.615 --> 00:14:56.868
<i>Hey, what gives?</i>
<i>I was hoping for a bigger reaction.</i>

00:14:58.660 --> 00:14:59.787
What's going on here?!

00:15:00.038 --> 00:15:02.831
- My head!
- <i>Oh! It's Kurosaki!</i>

00:15:03.541 --> 00:15:05.375
<i>Thank goodness!</i>

00:15:05.585 --> 00:15:07.461
<i>You're hurt,</i>
<i>but you look all right!</i>

00:15:07.711 --> 00:15:09.464
Inoue!
Thank goodness!

00:15:09.714 --> 00:15:10.631
You seem to be doing well!

00:15:11.173 --> 00:15:13.176
<i>Yeah, I'm all right!</i>

00:15:14.719 --> 00:15:15.761
<i>That you, Ichigo?</i>

00:15:15.845 --> 00:15:18.139
<i>Thank goodness you're safe.</i>

00:15:18.639 --> 00:15:22.434
That's my line.
I was worried too, you know.

00:15:22.769 --> 00:15:27.023
<i>Well, the truth is,</i>
<i>I wanted to contact you sooner,</i>

00:15:27.105 --> 00:15:28.607
<i>but a lot happened...</i>

00:15:28.857 --> 00:15:30.860
<i>Huh?</i>
<i>What are you guys doing in there?</i>

00:15:32.778 --> 00:15:34.238
That voice...
Could it be?

00:15:35.114 --> 00:15:37.616
- <i>That voice!</i>
- <i>Inoue! Sado!</i>

00:15:37.741 --> 00:15:38.618
<i>Kurosaki, you bastard!</i>

00:15:38.826 --> 00:15:40.244
<i>You're there, aren't you?!</i>

00:15:40.327 --> 00:15:41.620
- <i>No!</i>
- <i>Hey, why are you</i>

00:15:41.703 --> 00:15:43.456
- <i>He's not here!</i>
- <i>with that guy, Urahara?!</i>

00:15:43.581 --> 00:15:44.581
<i>Kurosaki...</i>

00:15:45.625 --> 00:15:48.669
As you can see,
we're all right.

00:15:49.294 --> 00:15:51.798
So please do what you have to do
for yourself...

00:15:52.631 --> 00:15:58.303
You can decide on your own...
what you truly want to do...

00:16:01.432 --> 00:16:04.059
<i>Oh, and don't worry about him.</i>

00:16:04.769 --> 00:16:06.895
<i>We reached a nice agreement.</i>

00:16:07.355 --> 00:16:08.648
<i>Well, see you later!</i>

00:16:11.900 --> 00:16:14.445
Was it okay to tell him that?

00:16:14.821 --> 00:16:16.114
Tell him what?

00:16:19.366 --> 00:16:23.705
If he does
what he truly wants to do...

00:16:24.371 --> 00:16:28.793
that will surely lead to
protecting us all in the end.

00:16:29.335 --> 00:16:33.798
But you two should know that
better than I do.

00:16:35.591 --> 00:16:36.717
And the person...

00:16:37.719 --> 00:16:42.014
who knows that better than anyone
is Kurosaki himself.

00:16:43.682 --> 00:16:44.767
Hey, Baldy...

00:16:45.100 --> 00:16:46.686
Oh!
You're talking to me?!

00:16:47.519 --> 00:16:51.898
If I go to this Royal Palace,
can I fix my Tensa Zangetsu?

00:16:52.775 --> 00:16:54.234
That's impossible.

00:16:54.317 --> 00:16:55.737
It can't be fixed.

00:16:56.695 --> 00:16:57.696
However...

00:16:57.864 --> 00:16:59.740
if you go to the Royal Palace,

00:16:59.824 --> 00:17:03.702
we can reforge it into something
resembling your original sword.

00:17:07.623 --> 00:17:08.624
Fine...

00:17:10.710 --> 00:17:12.711
Take me with you
to the Royal Palace!

00:17:14.588 --> 00:17:15.213
All right!

00:17:15.298 --> 00:17:17.299
"WELCOME TO
KUKAKU SHIBA'S RESIDENCE"
Time to launch!

00:17:17.759 --> 00:17:18.759
Huh?

00:17:20.010 --> 00:17:21.762
Go!

00:17:25.682 --> 00:17:28.269
Aren't there any seatbelts
in this thing?!

00:17:29.811 --> 00:17:30.688
There he goes.

00:17:31.271 --> 00:17:33.148
You sure it was
the right thing to do, Sis?!

00:17:34.025 --> 00:17:35.026
Yeah.

00:17:35.609 --> 00:17:37.028
If he doesn't go now,

00:17:37.319 --> 00:17:39.864
the Soul Society is finished
when the next invasion comes.

00:17:41.406 --> 00:17:43.116
We have no choice
but to let him go.

00:17:44.786 --> 00:17:48.830
Even if that means
making Uncle sad.

00:17:51.709 --> 00:17:53.086
All right, you guys!

00:17:53.169 --> 00:17:55.546
Get back to Kukaku's
Great Training Hall already!

00:17:55.922 --> 00:17:57.964
Help out with the training!

00:17:58.215 --> 00:18:01.719
Don't forget who took you off
the streets of the Rukon District.

00:18:02.678 --> 00:18:04.806
I'm getting tired of
her patronizing attitude...

00:18:04.888 --> 00:18:06.432
Agreed.

00:18:07.432 --> 00:18:08.726
Show some guts, Ganju.

00:18:09.602 --> 00:18:12.980
You can cry or scream, but I'm
throwing you into the next battle!

00:18:14.397 --> 00:18:15.398
Got it!

00:18:20.488 --> 00:18:22.280
Come on out, Ichigo Kurosaki!

00:18:23.699 --> 00:18:24.741
We've arrived!

00:18:24.991 --> 00:18:25.617
THE ROYAL PALACE

00:18:25.701 --> 00:18:27.787
THE ROYAL PALACE
This is the Royal Palace!

00:18:27.869 --> 00:18:29.955
THE ROYAL PALACE

00:18:36.711 --> 00:18:37.712
This is the place?

00:18:37.797 --> 00:18:38.588
That's right!

00:18:39.132 --> 00:18:40.258
Feel free to brag about it!

00:18:40.590 --> 00:18:44.929
Ordinary Soul Reapers
typically aren't allowed here!

00:18:45.846 --> 00:18:50.518
Though, I'm not sure if I can
call you an "ordinary" Soul Reaper...

00:18:51.102 --> 00:18:54.689
<i>So this is the place Aizen</i>
<i>so desperately wanted to come to...</i>

00:18:56.440 --> 00:18:57.441
Hold on a second!

00:18:57.650 --> 00:19:01.194
I thought you couldn't get into
the Royal Palace without the Ouken!

00:19:01.528 --> 00:19:03.280
Yeah, this is it.

00:19:03.865 --> 00:19:06.200
The Ouken refers to our bones,

00:19:06.241 --> 00:19:09.537
which were transformed
by the power of the Soul King

00:19:09.619 --> 00:19:12.789
when we were selected
to join Squad Zero.

00:19:13.249 --> 00:19:16.294
Therefore, there are two ways
to enter the Royal Palace...

00:19:16.711 --> 00:19:21.840
We either choose to allow you in
or you come in with us...

00:19:22.758 --> 00:19:25.553
Sosuke Aizen was
trying to make an Ouken.

00:19:25.635 --> 00:19:26.636
In other words...

00:19:27.137 --> 00:19:32.101
he was trying to create us
using his own spiritual powers.

00:19:32.977 --> 00:19:35.813
He schemed to
take the place of a god...

00:19:36.146 --> 00:19:39.400
by creating life
and killing the king...

00:19:41.527 --> 00:19:42.903
Sosuke Aizen...

00:19:43.570 --> 00:19:46.281
He truly is evil personified.

00:19:47.450 --> 00:19:50.118
But take this to heart,
Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:19:51.453 --> 00:19:53.663
The Quincies
that showed up this time

00:19:53.748 --> 00:19:56.209
are an even greater evil...

00:19:59.961 --> 00:20:02.548
All right.
Stand right there!

00:20:02.757 --> 00:20:04.508
Ready?
I'm about to blast you now.

00:20:04.592 --> 00:20:06.760
Don't move, or you'll die!

00:20:07.345 --> 00:20:08.887
Okay, here goes...!

00:20:09.096 --> 00:20:10.722
H-Hold on a second!

00:20:10.806 --> 00:20:13.267
- What is it?
- Where am I heading to?!

00:20:13.558 --> 00:20:14.935
Am I going to meet the Soul King?!

00:20:15.478 --> 00:20:17.939
Huh? Are you talking in your sleep
or something?!

00:20:18.064 --> 00:20:21.192
There's no way you'd be allowed
to meet the Soul King!

00:20:21.525 --> 00:20:23.693
- That hurts, damn it!
- Explain it to him properly!

00:20:23.778 --> 00:20:25.238
THE ROYAL PALACE - MAIN ENTRANCE
Listen closely.

00:20:25.320 --> 00:20:27.448
THE ROYAL PALACE - MAIN ENTRANCE
Right now,
we're at the main entrance.

00:20:27.530 --> 00:20:31.285
REIO GREATER PALACE
And over there is the main shrine,
the Reio Greater Palace.

00:20:31.368 --> 00:20:33.621
REIO GREATER PALACE
That's where the Soul King resides.

00:20:33.703 --> 00:20:34.204
REIO GREATER PALACE
And those five tray-like structures
floating around it

00:20:34.288 --> 00:20:38.041
SQUAD ZERO RIDEN
And those five tray-like structures
floating around it

00:20:38.125 --> 00:20:39.876
SQUAD ZERO RIDEN
are the Squad Zero Riden.

00:20:39.961 --> 00:20:41.753
SQUAD ZERO RIDEN
Those are our castles.

00:20:41.878 --> 00:20:44.464
Out of those...

00:20:44.923 --> 00:20:49.971
you'll be first going to
my Kirinden—all of you!

00:20:51.806 --> 00:20:52.807
"KIRINDEN"

00:20:56.018 --> 00:20:57.269
What the hell is this?!

00:20:57.728 --> 00:21:00.439
We're soaking in a hot spring,
of course.

00:21:00.522 --> 00:21:01.691
Why are you drowning them?!

00:21:01.773 --> 00:21:02.775
You're going to kill them!

00:21:03.150 --> 00:21:04.693
Wait!
He's bleeding!

00:21:04.902 --> 00:21:06.778
Quit your yapping.

00:21:07.320 --> 00:21:09.656
I'm soaking them in this hot water
to squeeze out

00:21:09.740 --> 00:21:11.784
their damaged Spiritual Pressure
along with their blood.

00:21:12.367 --> 00:21:13.911
Damaged Spiritual Pressure?

00:21:14.369 --> 00:21:16.622
You see that red hot spring
over there?

00:21:17.580 --> 00:21:18.082
"BLOOD POND HELL"

00:21:18.164 --> 00:21:19.834
"BLOOD POND HELL"
The sign says,
"Blood Pond Hell"...

00:21:19.916 --> 00:21:22.086
"BLOOD POND HELL"
So that Blood Pond Hell...

00:21:22.545 --> 00:21:26.589
We're going to take Byakuya,
who's completely squeezed out...

00:21:26.757 --> 00:21:28.092
and toss him in there!

00:21:28.759 --> 00:21:30.803
Hey!
He's on the verge of death!

00:21:30.845 --> 00:21:32.680
I told you to shut up!

00:21:33.221 --> 00:21:35.682
I draw out their blood
in White Bone Hell

00:21:35.766 --> 00:21:37.893
and replenish it
in Blood Pond Hell.

00:21:38.352 --> 00:21:40.145
I'll repeat this several times,

00:21:40.645 --> 00:21:43.857
and in the end, every drop of
bad blood and Spiritual Pressure

00:21:43.941 --> 00:21:46.777
in their bodies
will be swapped with my hot water!

00:21:47.278 --> 00:21:49.238
That's the way I heal others!

00:21:49.779 --> 00:21:51.699
Will doing this really work?

00:21:51.781 --> 00:21:53.241
Shut up and soak.

00:21:53.616 --> 00:21:55.368
With the kind of injuries you have,

00:21:56.494 --> 00:22:00.583
one night is enough to make you
feel twice as good as normal!

00:22:00.665 --> 00:22:02.751
"HOT SPRING DEMON" -
TENJIRO KIRINJI

00:22:10.259 --> 00:22:13.261
<i>Everything we had left behind</i>

00:22:13.429 --> 00:22:17.557
<i>Our breaths blending as mist</i>

00:22:17.641 --> 00:22:22.063
<i>without form or expression</i>

00:22:22.188 --> 00:22:26.358
<i>We lie buried as we glare</i>
<i>into the distance</i>

00:22:26.692 --> 00:22:29.319
<i>I can't hear anything</i>

00:22:29.444 --> 00:22:32.573
<i>I can't seem to cut anything</i>

00:22:32.698 --> 00:22:35.076
<i>It feels like I'm sinking</i>

00:22:35.201 --> 00:22:36.993
<i>Falling, falling</i>

00:22:37.118 --> 00:22:38.078
<i>Touching</i>

00:22:38.203 --> 00:22:41.582
<i>Eyes struck wide open</i>

00:22:41.664 --> 00:22:44.919
<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:22:45.044 --> 00:22:51.217
<i>The furthest reaches are now visible to us</i>

00:22:51.592 --> 00:22:55.221
<i>It cannot be undone</i>
<i>and cannot be stopped</i>

00:22:55.346 --> 00:22:58.682
<i>This ensuing struggle</i>

00:22:58.766 --> 00:23:03.479
<i>Whisk it away beyond</i>
<i>the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:03.604 --> 00:23:05.647
<i>Along with our breaths</i>

00:23:05.855 --> 00:23:07.148
<i>Take everything</i>

00:23:07.232 --> 00:23:11.987
<i>Whisk it away beyond</i>
<i>the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:12.113 --> 00:23:14.030
<i>Along with our futures</i>

00:23:14.155 --> 00:23:15.907
<i>Along with our world</i>

00:23:16.991 --> 00:23:20.203
<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:20.328 --> 00:23:26.585
<i>The furthest reaches are now</i>
<i>visible to us</i>

00:23:26.669 --> 00:23:28.671
<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:28.796 --> 00:23:30.588
<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:30.713 --> 00:23:34.093
<i>As we tear each other down</i>

00:23:44.644 --> 00:23:46.521
It seems you're awake...

00:23:47.272 --> 00:23:48.481
Soul King.

00:23:57.490 --> 00:24:00.243
<i>"Neither form nor soul</i>
<i>shall escape my blade..."</i>

00:24:02.413 --> 00:24:05.415
<i>"Nothing...except you."</i>

